OL,3,CTime to tax London tourists to help
OL,4,Cbankroll the capital?
OL,6,FLondon's mayor, Ken Livingstone, first
OL,7,Fbegan in office in 2000 becoming the
OL,8,Fmost powerful directly-elected
OL,9,Fpolitician in Britain.
OL,11,FBut successive governments have shown
OL,12,Flittle enthusiasm for handing the
OL,13,Fmayor more power.
OL,15,FBoris Johnson set up a finance
OL,16,Fcommission which floated the idea of
OL,17,FCity Hall keeping the proceeds of
OL,18,Fstamp duty. But his pitch came to
OL,19,Fnothing.
